&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;REGISTERED NURSE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent - Full and Part Time hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary range £24,907 to £30,615&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MAU are currently looking to recruit registered nurses. MAU is a friendly, supportive working environment and we are looking for highly motivated, enthusiastic and hardworking individuals; both experienced and newly qualified who can contribute to continuing our high standards of patient care.You will working over two areas, AAU (Acute Assessment Area) and AMU (Acute Medical Unit).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be expected to act as a positive role model to junior and unregistered staff, demonstrating an interest in the development of the unit and working towards maintaining and improving the standards of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to progress your own continuing professional development and gain specialist knowledge and skills in caring for acute medical patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for individuals with excellent communication and interpersonal skills, who can personally deliver a high standard of nursing care even under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In order to arrange such a visit, or to find out more about the role, please contact Sister Joanne Ballington on 01983 822099 ext 2249&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
